so we went to new york city today. (not yesterday like i thought.) oh my gosh i loved it there.
 we went to ground zero and it was so weird just trying to think of what it felt like on that day and all the chaos that was going on. it's hard to believe that it happened and it was almost four years ago, it still feels like just yesterday. there was a little memorial thing on the fence with all this information about 9/11, seeing all those names made me really sad..all those poor families they belonged to, it's still hard to believe that it happened. it had a little timeline thing on the fence with the times the planes took off and everything... idk i just tried to imagine what it was like there that day. 
and we went to battery park... saw the statue of liberty.  

i thought it was so cool walking past the subways and feeling the ground shake when a subway was under it. underground traveling. 

it was like a whole other world there. nothing like anywhere i have ever been before. when we were sitting in the traffic i looked outside at all the different people and thinking about how different their lifestyles are... there was a lady buying fruit and my mom and i were talking about her, thinking about how she lives and wondering where she goes home to and what she goes home to.. idk..it was cool looking at all the different people there.  

my dad was so happy to be there. it was like he was home. you could see the happiness in his eyes and you just tell that all these memories were running back to him. he told me he loved living there and there was something different to do there everyday. i think it would be amazing to live there.

i loved how it was so busy there. all the traffic. all the people walking on the sidewalks. it was truly fascinating.

i just had to breathe and take it all in.

i really don't understand how people hate it there. i really don't. people were not mean to us. we never got honked at. what is there to hate about it? i don't know.
i don't want to come home.
